        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When people look at a diamond ring, the first thing they notice is how much it shines. That sparkle is what makes diamond jewellery so special. While solitaire rings highlight a single diamond beautifully, halo rings take brilliance to another level.</p><p>A halo ring places small diamonds around the center stone, creating a circle or frame of sparkle. This design reflects more light and makes the entire ring look brighter. Because of this effect, halo rings have become one of the most popular choices for engagement rings and statement jewellery.</p><p>At Lucira Jewelry, halo designs are created to balance brilliance with elegant craftsmanship. From classic round halos to unique shapes like hexagon and oval designs, each ring brings its own personality while enhancing the beauty of the center diamond.</p><p>Let’s explore why halo rings continue to be loved by jewellery buyers around the world.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Halo Setting Naturally Enhances the Sparkle of the Center Diamond",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Halo Setting Naturally Enhances the Sparkle of the Center Diamond</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-halo",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_WfQaQ4": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/How_to_Style_a_Solitaire_Ring_for_Work_Without_Looking_Overdressed.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JMmk6L": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The biggest reason halo rings are so popular is simple: they shine more.</p><p>A halo setting surrounds the center diamond with smaller diamonds. When light hits the ring, it reflects off multiple stones instead of just one. This creates a brighter, more radiant look.</p><p>For example, the Intricate Halo Diamond Ring from Lucira shows how smaller diamonds around the center stone amplify the overall sparkle. The ring catches light from different angles, giving it a lively brilliance.</p><p>This design works especially well in indoor lighting, candlelight, and evening settings where diamonds reflect light beautifully.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Halo Rings Can Make the Center Diamond Appear Larger",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Halo Rings Can Make the Center Diamond Appear Larger</h2>",
            "custom_id": "halo-rings",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AH7kgb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Another reason people love halo rings is the illusion of size.</p><p>Because the halo surrounds the center stone with small diamonds, the entire top of the ring looks bigger. Even if the center diamond is modest in carat weight, the halo creates a fuller visual presence.</p><p>A design like the Illusion Square Halo Diamond Ring uses this effect cleverly. The surrounding diamonds expand the visual area of the ring, making the center stone appear larger than it actually is.</p><p>For many buyers, this means they can enjoy a bold-looking ring without needing a very large center diamond.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
